This paper is primarily focused on the analysis of the decoding latency of polar codes, which are a type of error-correcting code used in information theory. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory). Additionally, the paper involves analyzing the performance of algorithms for decoding polar codes, which could fall under cs.CC (Computational Complexity) or cs.SI (Systems and Control). The paper also involves numerical simulations, which could fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture).
